0},[94,685,231],{"class":549},[94,687,314],{"class":108},[94,689,112],{"class":549},[94,691,692,694,696],{"class":96,"line":228},[94,693,231],{"class":549},[94,695,305],{"class":108},[94,697,112],{"class":549},[94,699,700,702,705,707],{"class":96,"line":238},[94,701,542],{"class":100},[94,703,704],{"class":549},"\u002F",[94,706,583],{"class":108},[94,708,558],{"class":100},[17,710,711,712,714],{},"Finally, let's try visiting ",[31,713,33],{}," again and see what happens:",[17,716,717],{},[38,718],{"alt":719,"src":720},"header still comes through","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FXfCpx8E.png",[17,722,723,724,726,727,730,731,733,734,736,737,740,741,743],{},"So how does it work? Because we declared at the top of ",[31,725,33],{}," that we want to load the layout template (",[31,728,729],{},"{layout name=\"layout\" \u002F}","), ThinkPHP loads ",[31,732,494],{}," into ",[31,735,33],{}," and replaces ",[31,738,739],{},"{__CONTENT__}"," with the original ",[31,742,33],{}," content.",[17,745,746,747,749,750,752,753,755,756,759,760,530],{},"Of course, if you don't want to use ",[31,748,739],{}," and would rather use something fancier, ThinkPHP gives you another option — you just have to tell it where the content should go. For example, say my ",[31,751,494],{}," doesn't want to use ",[31,754,739],{}," but ",[31,757,758],{},"{__ONEFORALL__}"," instead (I've been watching too much My Hero Academia lately). Then you'd change ",[31,761,494],{},[85,763,765],{"className":87,"code":764,"language":89,"meta":90,"style":90},"{include file=\"index\u002Flayout\u002Fheader\" \u002F}\n[__ONEFORALL__] \u002F\u002F note: wrap it in []\n{include file=\"index\u002Flayout\u002Ffooter\" \u002F}\n",[31,766,767,771,776],{"__ignoreMap":90},[94,768,769],{"class":96,"line":97},[94,770,381],{"class":100},[94,772,773],{"class":96,"line":115},[94,774,775],{"class":100},"[__ONEFORALL__] \u002F\u002F note: wrap it in []\n",[94,777,778],{"class":96,"line":135},[94,779,463],{"class":100},[17,781,782,783,785,786,789],{},"And the layout import inside ",[31,784,33],{},"? You use ",[31,787,788],{},"replace"," to tell ThinkPHP which chunk we're going to parse and swap out, so you'd write it like this:",[85,791,793],{"className":87,"code":792,"language":89,"meta":90,"style":90},"{layout name=\"layout\" replace=\"[__ONEFORALL__]\" \u002F}\n\u003Ch1>{$title}\u003C\u002Fh1>\n{volist name=\"user\" id=\"list\"}\n\u003Cul>\n  \u003Cli>Name:{$list.name}\u003C\u002Fli>\n  \u003Cli>Weight:{$list.weight}\u003C\u002Fli>\n  \u003Cli>Height:{$list.height}\u003C\u002Fli>\n\u003C\u002Ful>\n{\u002Fvolist}\n",[31,794,795,800,812,816,824,836,848,860,868],{"__ignoreMap":90},[94,796,797],{"class":96,"line":97},[94,798,799],{"class":100},"{layout name=\"layout\" replace=\"[__ONEFORALL__]\" \u002F}\n",[94,801,802,804,806,808,810],{"class":96,"line":115},[94,803,118],{"class":100},[94,805,287],{"class":104},[94,807,221],{"class":100},[94,809,287],{"class":104},[94,811,112],{"class":100},[94,813,814],{"class":96,"line":135},[94,815,298],{"class":100},[94,817,818,820,822],{"class":96,"line":145},[94,819,118],{"class":100},[94,821,305],{"class":104},[94,823,112],{"class":100},[94,825,826,828,830,832,834],{"class":96,"line":164},[94,827,148],{"class":100},[94,829,314],{"class":104},[94,831,317],{"class":100},[94,833,314],{"class":104},[94,835,112],{"class":100},[94,837,838,840,842,844,846],{"class":96,"line":189},[94,839,148],{"class":100},[94,841,314],{"class":104},[94,843,330],{"class":100},[94,845,314],{"class":104},[94,847,112],{"class":100},[94,849,850,852,854,856,858],{"class":96,"line":213},[94,851,148],{"class":100},[94,853,314],{"class":104},[94,855,343],{"class":100},[94,857,314],{"class":104},[94,859,112],{"class":100},[94,861,862,864,866],{"class":96,"line":228},[94,863,231],{"class":100},[94,865,305],{"class":104},[94,867,112],{"class":100},[94,869,870],{"class":96,"line":238},[94,871,360],{"class":100},[17,873,874],{},"And the result is the same — the layout gets pulled in just fine:",[17,876,877],{},[38,878],{"alt":879,"src":880},"pulled in successfully","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FDlAGx5T.png",[17,882,883,884,887,888,895],{},"You can also tweak things through ",[31,885,886],{},"config\u002Ftemplate.php",", and you can even use a Controller to decide which layout gets output. For the full details, check the official ",[889,890,894],"a",{"href":891,"rel":892},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.kancloud.cn\u002Fmanual\u002Fthinkphp5_1\u002F354079",[893],"nofollow","developer manual"," (in Mandarin) — I'm only covering the common approaches here.",[12,897,899],{"id":898},"wrapping-up","Wrapping up",[17,901,902],{},"From this post you can see that ThinkPHP's built-in template engine is actually plenty good enough. Unless you've got some special requirement, I'd generally just recommend sticking with the built-in one. Next up I'll cover ThinkPHP + Bootstrap, which ties in nicely with the Layout technique from this post — that way the effect will be a lot easier to see.",[904,905,906],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}",{"title":90,"searchDepth":115,"depth":115,"links":908},[909,910,911,912,913],{"id":14,"depth":115,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":115,"text":23},{"id":363,"depth":115,"text":364},{"id":487,"depth":115,"text":488},{"id":898,"depth":115,"text":899},"PHP","2019-09-20 09:52:03","ThinkPHP ships with its own HTML template engine, so this time we'll look at how to build a Layout with it. We'll split a page into header and footer, pull them in with the include syntax, and then level up to a proper layout file with a CONTENT placeholder. By the end you'll see that the built-in template engine is honestly good enough for most projects.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002Fthinkphp-day-19-layout","3",{"title":6,"description":916},false,"en\u002FPHP\u002Fthinkphp-day-19-layout",[914,927,928,929,930],"MySQL","ThinkPHP 5.1","Learning ThinkPHP from Scratch","11th iThome Ironman Contest",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F20\u002Fthinkphp-day-19-layout\u002F","-T1ildEXrBYFn621XmqXr2wZgcjwE_aSyuf8OSKvmlc",{"newer":935,"older":939},{"url":936,"title":937,"date":938},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F21\u002Fthinkphp-day-20-import-bootstrap\u002F","Learning ThinkPHP from Scratch Day 20 - Pulling Bootstrap into Your Layout","2019-09-21 00:01:05",{"url":940,"title":941,"date":942},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F09\u002F20\u002Fjs-from-zero-05-arrays-and-objects\u002F","RE: Learning JS from Zero — Day 5: Arrays and Objects","2019-09-20 09:51:00",[944,949,953],{"url":945,"title":946,"date":947,"readingMinutes":948},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2022\u002F04\u002F17\u002Fmac-xampp-apache-wont-start-fix\u002F","Fixing Mac XAMPP Apache Won't Start","2022-04-17 14:32:41","2",{"url":950,"title":951,"date":952,"readingMinutes":922},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F02\u002Fthinkphp-day-31-the-end-is-just-another-beginning\u002F","Day 31 - Learning ThinkPHP From Scratch: The End Is Just Another Beginning","2019-10-02 00:00:02",{"url":954,"title":955,"date":956,"readingMinutes":957},"\u002Fen\u002Fphp\u002F2019\u002F10\u002F01\u002Fthinkphp-day-30-deploy-to-heroku\u002F","Day 30 - Learning Thin